<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-029-175 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 476 062</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Weekly  Oct 24 1991 p13(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>ATandamp;T remains bullish despite $1.8bn losses. (billion) (thirdquarter, 1991)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>ATandamp;T announces it has posted losses of $1.8 billion for 3rd qtr1991.andP;  This is after accepting charges of $4 billion to covercosts associated with the acquisition of computer manufacturer NCRCorp. The costs also cover the 14,000 redundancies it initiated inits telecommunications business.andP;  ATandamp;T expects to post a profitfor the fiscal year.andP;  The work force reductions will continuethrough 1994.andP;  Without the heavy costs, the company claims that itwould have posted profits higher than those of the same period in1990.andP;  For the quarter, ATandamp;T by itself and without costs, postedprofits of $808 million, mainly from improved profit margins andits telecommunications services.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (Finance)NCR Corp. (Acquisitions, mergers, divestments).andO;Topic:     AcquisitionFinancial ReportLossesThird QuarterRevenueComputer industry.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>